                    <span>This book perhaps is the easiest to read and understand. Kind of step-by-step tutorials. Each chapter is followed by a useful sample. Some useful and interesting stuff on Web development using GDI+ and printing. Chapters are organized very well. I would add more complex samples. Rest is pretty straight forward. Overall an interesting reading. If you are trying to understand GDI+ classes, not bad at all.</span>
                  
